Rating: 4
I made this today for my dad's birthday and it was excellent. I buy fresh ginger from my local Asian supermarket, which only sells it in wrapped packages of a quarter pound or so. That's a LOT of ginger, so I cut it into 1" pieces and put it into a jar and cover with dry sherry. I keep it in the fridge and it lasts a couple of years this way. This is the ginger I used in the gingerbread today and it was superb. Thanks for the recipe!

