Rating: 4
After reading the reviews, I followed the recipe with these modifications: add 1/4 tsp of cloves, used 2 Tbl of pureed ginger and one tsp of powdered ginger. I served it with whipped cream made with a pint of heavy whipping cream, Tbl white sugar, dash of vanilla and indispensable packet of Whipit stabilizer (apologies to purists). Brought it to the same Thanksgiving crowd as last year when I made "Childhood Gingerbread with Molasses." Gingerbread was requested (and enjoyed last year) but this time everyone EXCLAIMED how excellent it was and complimented me. I vastly prefer it over last year's gingerbread.

Rating: 3
I used an 8" square pan instead of a 9, which I think was a bad idea. The cake was slightly dry around the edges and still undercooked in the very center. I also didn't have enough fresh ginger so I used 1 tbsp fresh and subbed the other 2 tbsps with 1/4" tsp ground ginger. The cake was good and everyone loved it but I have made better recipes in the past. I also made caramel and whipped cream to serve with it, which is really wonderful.

