Rating: 4
I think this is a great base recipe. Normally, I like to try a recipe once before altering it, but I read all the reviews and decided I should increase the ginger amount. I substituted ground ginger for ground cinnamon and omitted allspice completely. I added a smidgen of vanilla to the butter mixture. I added 1/2 cup of crystallized ginger chips(from www.gingerpeople.com) to the flour mixture. I think it's delicious! I like the lighter texture, as well. It's definitely very gingery!

